AGI - US President, Donald Trump>, declared exclusively to Breitbart that his recent conversations with the presidents of Russia and Ukraine, Vladimir Putin and Volodymyr Zelensky, were "two very good calls". >"I believe that an agreement will be reached, so we can end the bloodshed that is happening there," added Trump.&nbsp;
"My goal is to put these two countries at the table. Then we will work for a ceasefire and eventually we will stop losing 2,000 people a week. Two thousand people a week or more are killed in that war, and I want to stop it," Trump said. "I also want to stop the huge funding we need. I also want Europe to pay as much as we do because it has not done so with Biden and Biden never asked because Biden was a very incompetent president."
Much of the discussion with the Ukrainian president was based on the previous dialogue with Vladimir Putin>. "We're really on the road," Trump said. The White House also confirmed the relevance of the call, with spokesman Karoline Leavitt > who said: "We have never been so close to peace and this thanks to President Trump." For his part, Zelensky reiterated the importance of collaboration between Ukraine and the United States for a lasting resolution of the conflict with Russia. "We believe that together with America and under the leadership of President Trump we can reach a lasting peace this year," he wrote about X.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. and Ukraine negotiating teams will meet again in Gedda in the coming days to discuss technical details regarding the implementation of the ceasefire and the preparation of a peace agreement. "We sent our representatives to work as quickly as possible," Zelensky confirmed.
According to the White House, Trump proposed that energy plants pass under US control, claiming that "the American property of these power plants would be the best protection for such infrastructure and support for Ukrainian energy infrastructure," said Leavitt. However, confirmations have not yet emerged on a possible acceptance by Kiev.&nbsp;
Zelensky reiterated that he had not suffered any pressure from Trump > to grant favors to Russia. "I didn't hear any pressure. This is a fact," said the Ukrainian leader, closing the interview report. In the evening, finally, the Ukrainian leader announced that he will fly to France next week.
<h2>Ue: draft at 26, commitment to continue to support defence
The twenty-seven Heads of State or Government of the European Union return to Brussels for the third time in six weeks (plus a video conference summit). Once again the goal is to show unity in support of Ukraine and in giving the European bloc a new independent defence posture from the United States and able to face the Russian threat. However, cracks begin to emerge. The declaration on Ukraine will come - for the second time - adopted to twenty-six due to the opposition of the Hungarian prime minister, Viktor Orban.
"Recalling its previous conclusions, the European Council reaffirms its continuous and unwavering support for the independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of Ukraine within its internationally recognized borders. The European Union maintains its approach to "peace through force", which requires Ukraine to be in the strongest possible position, with its solid military and defence capabilities as an essential component. In line with this approach, the European Union remains committed, in coordination with partners and related allies, to provide additional full support to Ukraine and its people, while exercising its intrinsic right to self-defense against the war of aggression of Russia". It is what we read in the draft of the statement to twenty-six of which the AGI has seen.
<h2>Trump, the EU should be our friend but treats us very badly
The European Union "would be a friend" of the United States but "she treats us very badly" in the commercial field, Trump said in the interview with Breitbart. Asked about the Imec - the economic corridor between India, the Middle East and Europe that stands as an alternative to the Chinese Silk Road - the head of the White House has spoken of a "group of wonderful nations" that unite "in contrast to other countries who want to hit us on trade", but without ever naming China. "We have a powerful group of business partners," Trump said, "yet, we cannot allow these partners to treat us badly. Frankly, from many points of view we find ourselves better with our opponents than with our friends. Those who should not be friendly with us in some cases treat us better than those who should be, like the European Union, who treats us in a terrible way on trade."
<h2> Russia: Trump, distension could remove it from China</h2>
A détente between the United States and Russia could remove Moscow from China, although Washington has not placed this goal nor is it trying to reach a peace in Ukraine for this purpose," said the American president. A detachment of Russia from Beijing "would be a consequence of this, or not, I think it's a good thing," Trump answered a question about it.&nbsp;
