The Chp called a new event for this evening. On Wednesday, thousands of people gathered before the headquarters of the commune by launching slogans against the government of President Recep Tayyip Erdogan>. A spontaneous gathering, to show solidarity to the mayor and happened despite the 4 days of prohibition of demonstrations decreed by the Istanbul prosecutor.
<div </div
Some roads and metro, bus and funicular stops have been closed, disembarked by transennes and the police in riots. At the event he also took part the wife of the mayor of Istanbul, Dilek Imamoglu, who turned to the crowd stating that "it was not only Ekrem Imamoglu to end in prison, but 16 million citizens".
Words that have unleashed the applause of the crowd that has asked loudly the resignation of the government.&nbsp;Imamoglu is considered the natural challenger of the president in office and should have participated in the primaries of his party scheduled for next Sunday. As happened on Wednesday, even today there is no access to social media> as Instagram and messaging services like WhatsApp.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, the Turkish lira continues to suffer the consequences of the events of the last 24 hours. After touching the historical minimum compared to the dollar and euro yesterday, today, despite small signs of recovery, the evaluation remains very low: in fact serve 38 lire for a dollar and 41 lire for a euro. A collapse that could have heavy political consequences for the same Erdogan.&nbsp;
